/* STDLIB/iii/aether/xeno_cli.iii -- iii xeno: THE OPEN SPACE, driven.
 *
 *   iii xeno fair <N>              THE FAIRNESS ARM: roundtrip the first N steps of
 *                                  the universal enumeration + spot-encode every
 *                                  carrier; exit 3 on any break.  This is the
 *                                  anti-rigging theorem, machine-checked live.
 *   iii xeno census <n>            the exact iso-class census of carrier n by TWO
 *                                  INDEPENDENT ROUTES: explicit canonical dedup
 *                                  (organ) vs Burnside fixed-point counting (CLI,
 *                                  separate code).  Exit 7 iff they disagree.
 *   iii xeno anchor <lawfuel>      the machine's own algebra (the silicon point,
 *                                  via substrate_ontogenesis), its exact seat in
 *                                  the universal enumeration (n<=5 exact; else
 *                                  class-only, named), and its open-law theory.
 *   iii xeno sweep <fuel> <lawfuel>  the dovetail: visit structures fairly, canon-
 *                                  dedup, decide the first lawfuel open laws on
 *                                  every NEW class by total exhaustion, search
 *                                  anchor homomorphisms, print the law demography
 *                                  + drain + XENO_CERT (deterministic fold).
 *   iii xeno check <fuel>          the whole arm battery (fair, census x2, judge
 *                                  two-path, canon<->profile consistency, replay
 *                                  determinism, vacuity refusal).
 *
 * Exit: 0 OK | 1 usage | 2 env | 3 FAIRNESS BROKEN | 5 VACUOUS (refused)
 *     | 6 INTERNAL DISAGREEMENT (two-path) | 7 CENSUS MISMATCH | 8 NONDETERMINISM.
 * NIH: composes xeno_ontogenesis + substrate_ontogenesis (the anchor) +
 * mathesis_ontogenesis/mathesis_forge (the independent profile lens).
 * Hexad: kind_essence.  Ring: R0. */
module xeno_cli

